race.comment: SINDEE (1) was last seen winning over 1400m here on March 8. She is unbeaten here and has had some local jumpouts to help get her ready for her return. She remains in the same class, and only needs the gaps at the right time to have the last say fresh up in this. COOPER (6) returns after a six-month break, and it's worth noting he grabbed a minor placing first-up last prep over 1200m at Waverley. He has a good record on this track, including a couple of wins, and as a winner of his latest trial, he will be ready to rumble fresh. HASSTOBEFAST (2) finished sixth, three lengths off the winner, in a 1200m race at Tauranga three weeks back. 1400m is at the top of her limit, but with the right run, she is worth including in all top 4 combos. PARTY ROCKING (4) has been out of the money in a couple of runs since finishing second fresh up in September on the Awapuni poly track. He only needs a firmer turf surface here to be back in the money. KERETI (9) is usually very consistent. Include.
